 change the face of the stock. Investors will be happy to see that happen. From the chart, Fidson has been on an uptrend. It is a sign of strength… The year Fidson got to such price was around April 2008. Before now, its audited results come around that period. Now that we are seeing improved numbers, it should tell us what we are likely to see from the stock going forward. That is going to support the price movement… already it’s on a strong uptrend, which you have seen here. And, the good thing is that the MACD in Fidson is very positive… For me, therefore, if you are in Fidson, you don’t need to disturb yourself, just hold your position and watch. However, if you have achieved your target in terms of profit, there is no need to change the goal post. Sell 50 percent of your position and watch. Once the price touches your target, you may not sell everything, because you see momentum in Fidson, you can dispose of half and watch the momentum go. Don’t be greedy and say you are still making money and don’t want to sell at all. For me, there are still positive sentiments for Fidson. In this stock, observe the three or four things I always tell you about: Positive sentiments, earnings growth, good market fundamentals, and the price is charging up, all of which have confirmed our strategy in Investdata. Also, you must lookout for a stock that has good volume… the volume is going up relatively, especially if you remember that volume in the stock has not always been much. Let’s watch what happens next week, and even if you notice profit-taking in Fidson, don’t panic out, because it will still rebound, especially when the full-year result is released and the board declares a dividend. Remember that Fidson paid about 25 kobo dividends last year. I see the directors paying 35 kobo or even more this time around. But the earnings we have seen in Q3 is already indicating where the company is going. Fidson is a stock to hold, because, despite its performance so far, the healthcar